// probectl Go workspace.
//
// The repository is a monorepo built around a single primary module
// (github.com/imfeelingtheagi/probectl: cmd/, internal/, pkg/) plus a separate
// integration-test module (./test) whose heavier, test-only dependencies are
// intentionally kept out of the main module's go.mod / go.sum. The workspace
// ties them together for local development and CI; production builds use each
// module's own go.mod. Additional modules (e.g. a future public SDK) can be
// added with `go work use ./<dir>` without disturbing existing imports.
// The language version is pinned to 1.26.4 to MATCH both modules' go.mod
// (go 1.26.4). go.work must stay in lockstep with go.mod: a bare `go 1.26`
// here is OLDER than the modules' `go >= 1.26.4`, which Go rejects whenever it
// cannot auto-resolve a newer toolchain — i.e. under GOTOOLCHAIN=local, as the
// FIPS distribution build (`make build-fips`) runs. That skew broke the
// build-fips CI job; keeping the two in sync is SUPPLY-007.
go 1.26.4

// Pin the build toolchain to a patched Go (stdlib fixes for GO-2026-5037
// crypto/x509 + GO-2026-5039 net/textproto) — the minimum toolchain CI and dev
// builds resolve to (matches the go line above and each module's go.mod).
toolchain go1.26.4

use (
	.
	./test
)
